  <title>Add folders to the desktop</title>
  <p>You can add folders to your desktop to organize your apps.</p>

  <comment>{video 2}</comment>

  <steps>
    <title>To add a new folder:</title>
    <item>
      <p>Right-click on the desktop and select <gui>Add folder</gui>.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Pick an icon for your new folder.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Type a name for your new folder (for example, "School") and hit
      <key>Enter</key>.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>You have added a new folder to the desktop. Great! Now click on the
      <media its:translate="no" type="image" mime="image/png" src="figures/eos-icon-app-store-close.png">X</media>
      on the top-right of the window to go back to the desktop.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Drag and drop the apps you want into your folder.</p>
    </item>
  </steps>

